      "message": "I think now we want to get slightly fancier in here too, so that we always make sure to use every last byte (e.g. use the last 3 bytes to fill out a uint32_t instead of just returning 0).\n\nif (fNextByte + sizeof(T) \u003e fBytes-\u003esize()) {\n    T n \u003d 0;\n    memcpy(\u0026n, fBytes-\u003ebytes() + fNextByte, fBytes-\u003esize() - fNextByte);\n    fNextByte \u003d fBytes-\u003esize();\n    return n;\n}\nT n;\nmemcpy(\u0026n, fBytes-\u003ebytes() + fNextByte, sizeof(T));\nfNextByte +\u003d sizeof(T);\nreturn n;\n\n(Some of that duplicated code is me being paranoid about keeping the normal past fast.)",
